Sandwich: slices of smoked salmon and fresh mango on a crusty, avocado-smeared baguette. The sandwich was light yet filling. However, a drizzle of sour vinaigrette would have really rounded out the flavors. The fries were divine. Petite Abeille and Five Guys are two of the few places where I enjoy fries as the default side dish. Get the complete review at appetu.de/utfEq8. Appetude's blog.
